                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d866">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">654.116/59: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-05-29T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 29, 1936—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>46. Despatch 424, May 19, 1936, from Zurich.<note n="11" xml:id="d866fn11">Not
                        printed.</note> Please collect at once all pertinent facts and such
                    documentary evidence as is available tending to show that a new and special tax
                    has been imposed upon imports of American lard into Switzerland. Telegraph
                    whether in your opinion this tax is in violation of Article I of trade agreement
                    and on what grounds you base your opinion. Upon receipt of this information the
                    Department will instruct you what representations it desires you to make to the
                    Swiss Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
